						<summary>

						<p>The first half of the inscription is badly damaged. This seems to record an agreement given by the <hi rend="italic">Ūrār</hi> of Paḷgūr to measure out annually in the temple. 93 <hi rend="italic">kāḍi</hi> and odd of paddy (as interest) for the 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold which they had received from some donor whose name is lost.</p>						

						</summary>
